CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 29, 1950, pg. 20, reads: "Look Out, Dusty, You're Making Headlines - Dusty Freeman, well-known comic, engages in a little 'quiet romance' with Mrs. 'Tick' Jones in his dressing room backstage at the Casino Theatre completely unaware that Lynee Doty, editor and chief reporter for the Harlem on Parade Dispatch, is getting an eyeful from beneath his dressing table. Miss Doty, also a chorus member of Dusty's 'Harlem on Parade Revue,' which appeared all last week at the Casino, began editing the paper to create a diversion for the fifteen-member cast. The item on Dusty, however, is all in fun. Mrs. Jones is the wife of Dusty's son, also a member of the troupe."
TitMainTitle: Entertainer "Tick" Jones seated on lap of comic Dusty Freeman with Lynee Doty dressed as reporter and kneeling on floor beside them, in dressing room of Casino Theater during "Harlem on Parade Revue"
